    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add Atomic Model Rename to Ollama\n\n**4 files, 7 targeted insertions — zero existing code changed.**\n\n---\n\n### What I found\n\nAll required imports (`manifest`, `errtypes`, `model`, `os`, `fmt`, `errors`, `io`) are already present in `server/routes.go` — no new imports needed in any file.\n\n---\n\n### Implementation steps\n\n**Step 1 — `api/types.go` (after line 765, after `CopyRequest`)**\nAdd `RenameRequest` struct with identical shape to `CopyRequest`:\n```go\n// RenameRequest is the request passed to [Client.Rename].\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2 — `api/client.go` (after line 387, after `Copy()`)**\nAdd `Rename()` method — same structure as `Copy()`, POST to `/api/rename`:\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    if err := c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil); err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3 — `server/routes.go` (after line 1483, after `CopyHandler`)**\nAdd `RenameHandler` with this logic:\n1. Bind JSON → 400 on bad body\n2. Empty `Source`/`Destination` → 400\n3. `model.ParseName()` + `.IsValid()` on both → 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` succeeds (err == nil) → **409 Conflict** \"destination model 'X' already exists\"\n5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404 if `os.ErrNotExist`, 500 on other errors\n6. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` (exact `DeleteHandler` pattern, lines 1084–1103) → 500 on failure\n7. Return 200 `{\"status\": \"success\"}`\n\n**Step 4 — `server/routes.go` (line 1699, after `/api/copy`)**\n```go\nr.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)\n```\n\n**Step 5 — `cmd/cmd.go` (after line 1350, after `CopyHandler`)**\nAdd `RenameHandler` func — mirror of `CopyHandler`, calls `client.Rename()`, prints `Renamed \"<source>\" to \"<destination>\"`.\n\n**Step 6 — `cmd/cmd.go` (after line 2263, after `copyCmd`)**\nAdd `renameCmd`:\n```go\nrenameCmd := &cobra.Command{\n    Use:     \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\",\n    Short:   \"Rename a model\",\n    Args:    cobra.ExactArgs(2),\n    PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat,\n    RunE:    RenameHandler,\n}\n```\n\n**Step 7 — `cmd/cmd.go`: Register `renameCmd`**\n- In the flags-configuration loop (line ~2295): add `renameCmd` after `copyCmd`\n- In `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` (line ~2345): add `renameCmd` after `copyCmd`",
